<emphasis id="B921EAAA992444740782FEE97A5DFEC2" bold="true" box="[199,335,296,323]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Comments.</emphasis>
Below locality labels the following labels are also attached on the 
<typeStatus id="54EE881A992444740373FEE87F8AFEC2" box="[1078,1176,297,323]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">holotype</typeStatus>
“Typus// 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B992444740241FEE87BAAFEE6" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">Apenesia laevis</taxonomicName>
K.// 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B9924447407ABFE8C7A64FEE6" authority="Kieff." authorityName="Kieff." box="[238,374,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevis">laevis Kieff.</taxonomicName>
// 
<typeStatus id="54EE881A9924447406C9FE8C7AE6FEE6" box="[396,500,333,359]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Syntypus</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="9D53FD319924447406BFFE8C791DFEE6" box="[506,527,333,359]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B99244474055FFE8C7997FEE6" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[538,645,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apenesia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B9924447405CAFE8C7880FEE6" authority=", J. J. Kieffer, 1904" authorityName=", J. J. Kieffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[655,914,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levis">levis, J. J. Kieffer, 1904</taxonomicName>
// Museo Civico di Genova”. These labels were added to the specimen when Dr. Poggi organized the Kieffer collection in MSNG (personal communication). Another apterous female in MSGN with identical locality label to 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B99244474041FFE5478E8FE2E" authorityName=", J. J. Kieffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[858,1018,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levis">
<emphasis id="B921EAAA99244474041FFE5478E8FE2E" box="[858,1018,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Apenesia levis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
received an extra label “ 
<typeStatus id="54EE881A99244474024BFE547E6BFE2E" box="[1294,1401,405,431]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Syntypus</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="9D53FD319924447402C5FE547E87FE2E" box="[1408,1429,405,431]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B9924447407D2FE787A10FE52" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[151,258,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Apenesia</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B992444740648FE787900FE52" authority=", J. J. Kieffer, 1904" authorityName=", J. J. Kieffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[269,530,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levis">levis, J. J. Kieffer, 1904</taxonomicName>
// Museo Civico di Genova” when Dr. Poggi was organizing Kieffer’s 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B992444740266FE787E8EFE52" box="[1315,1436,441,467]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bethylidae</taxonomicName>
collection. Kieffer (1904). However, he described this species based on a unique specimen. In this paper, whenever Kieffer described species based on more than one specimen he stated it explicitly in material examined. Further, the second exemplar with a 
<typeStatus id="54EE881A99244474068AFDE47934FDBE" box="[463,550,549,575]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">syntype</typeStatus>
label of 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B9924447405CDFDE479C8FDBE" authorityName=", J. J. Kieffer" authorityYear="1904" box="[648,730,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="levis">
<emphasis id="B921EAAA9924447405CDFDE479C8FDBE" box="[648,730,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">A. levis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is actually belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B992444740491FDE47F7FFDBE" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1809" box="[980,1133,549,575]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Sclerodermus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAAA992444740491FDE47F7FFDBE" box="[980,1133,549,575]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Sclerodermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with large developed eyes, although ocelli are obliterated. Here we conclude that the 
<typeStatus id="54EE881A99244474046CFD887899FDE2" box="[809,907,585,611]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">holotype</typeStatus>
examined by Kieffer was clearly the 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D3B992444740273FD887E8FFDE2" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1874" box="[1334,1437,585,611]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Apenesia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B921EAAA992444740273FD887E8FFDE2" box="[1334,1437,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Apenesia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
redescribed in this study. The other specimen was incorrectly labeled and both were wrongly labeled as 
<typeStatus id="54EE881A992444740267FDAC7E6FFD06" box="[1314,1405,621,647]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">syntype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
